Goals:
1. Demo / prototype i salgsøjemed
2. Muligheder begrænsninger ift. native app eller react-native
3. Præsentation af findings internt; udadtil; SoMo; blogspot; evt. video


--


Technical features:
1. Offline capabilities
2. Native 'like' (vibration, homescreen. butter smooth 60fps)
3. Push notification
4. UI gestures (pinching, swapping, dragging, pulling, etc.) (FOKUS)
5. SVG morphing icons
6. IndexDB or alternative way to persist state 
7. Pull to refresh behavior (https://developers.google.com/web/updates/2017/11/overscroll-behavior)
8. Drag and drop behavior
9. Async. work and syncronisation 
10. Fluid transition?
11. Card slider
12. Routing 
13. Loading screen
14. Camera with image recognition (upload capability)

Problems:
1. Safe zones
2. Browser vs in-app mode
3. Phone distinction
4. Scroll hijack switching (while dragging, disable scroll down, etc.)

--


Learnings:
1. Clear distinction of where and how pwa excels compared to native and reverse


--


1. Food app (consisting of fruits, nuts, vegetables, milky products, meat)
2. Detail page (with food declaration)
3. List page (different food options in groups, sorting, filtering, search)
4. Profile page with credit card settings, and delivery information
5. Opskrifter (samvirke)
6. Køb en ret (bestående af retter + opskrift + næring)

--

- DrawIO tree routing structure
- Figma mock up
- Routing, icons, responsive styles for mobile
- Fooding scraping / constructing food object,  



